item.title: My Exciting News!
item.description:
My Exciting News!
Hello everyone, I am so excited with this announcement! I've been a supporter of Lancome ever since my mother bought their products at the department store and gave me their sample sized items. Now, I am the official Lancome video makeup artist. I will make 1 video a month using their products showcasing different looks, trends, backstage events and more! Nothing has changed except for an addition of 1 special Lancome Video a month. =) I am so excited to start this amazing journey with a brand I trust and respect so much. I truly am honored and grateful. I would not have made it here if it wasn't for you, my supporters. I also think it's amazing how Lancome is supportive of all race and culture. item.title: Tracy Porter's Interception In Super Bowl 44...According to Tecmo Super Bowl
item.description:
Tracy Porter's Interception In Super Bowl 44...According to Tecmo Super Bowl
The New Orleans Saints faced the Indianapolis Colts in Super Bowl 44. With 3:24, the Colts were down by 7 and driving hoping to tie up the game and potentially force overtime. On a throw from Peyton Manning to Reggie Wayne, Saints cornerback Tracy Porter jumped the route and took the interception to the endzone for a touchdown, effectively putting the dagger in the Colts en route for to a Saint Super Bowl victory. This is that play, if it happened on Tecmo Super Bowl. Audio is the CBS TV feed of Jim Nantz and the blithering idiot that is Phil Simms. (As a Colts fan, this was tough to make, also tough because of my video software being teh suck (That's why the zoom ins aren't great) and because INTs are hard to replicate.
